This document describes how to install the OFDPA software provided in
this package on the Agema AGC7648 switch.

Pre-requisites:  The switch must have ONL(Open Network Linux) installed via ONIE.
    Must log in as user root, password is onl
    All commands run as root user.

Downloading and running OFDPA
============================================================
* download the OFDPA package
    root@localhost:~# tftp IPaddress
    tftp> binary
    tftp> get ofdpa-agc7648a_0.3.0.3.1_amd64.deb
    tftp> quit
   
* Install the OFDPA package
    root@localhost:~# dpkg -i ofdpa-agc7648a_0.3.0.3.1_amd64.deb

    Note:  It may be necessary to run the following command before installing
           OFDPA because sometimes the ONIE install leaves some packages
           in a half-configured state:

           dpkg --configure -a

* Insert kernel modules and launch ofdpa, then the switch will be ready to run anyone of the applications. 
    root@localhost:~# cd /broadcom/ofdpa
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# mknod /dev/linux-kernel-bde c 127 0
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# mknod /dev/linux-user-bde c 126 0
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# insmod linux-kernel-bde.ko
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# insmod linux-user-bde.ko
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# ./ofdpa &
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# ./client_drivshell ps


* Breakout to 100G, 40G, 25G or 10G configuration
    root@localhost:~# cd  /broadcom/ofdpa
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# cp -af 100G-ofdpa_rc.cfg ofdpa_rc.cfg    //for breakout to 100G
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# cp -af 40G-ofdpa_rc.cfg ofdpa_rc.cfg     //for breakout to 40G
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# cp -af 25G-ofdpa_rc.cfg ofdpa_rc.cfg     //for breakout to 25G
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# cp -af 10G-ofdpa_rc.cfg ofdpa_rc.cfg     //for breakout to 10G
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# ./ofdpa &
    root@localhost:/broadcom/ofdpa# ./client_drivshell ps

